FBIS4-51225 "drchi102_v_94005" FBIS-CHI-94-102 Daily Report 26 May 1994 TAIWAN Niger President To Visit Beginning 2 June Niger President To Visit Beginning 2 June OW2605103594 Taipei CNA in English 0716 GMT 26 May 94 OW2605103594 Taipei CNA English BFN [By Lilian Wu] [Text] Taipei, May 26 (CNA) -- Niger President Mahamane Ousmane will visit the Republic of China [ROC] next week at the invitation of ROC President Li Teng-hui, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs said. During his stay in Taiwan June 2-7, Ousmane will sign a joint communique with Li to reaffirm friendly relations between the two countries. Ousmane will also discuss with Li issues of mutual concern and visit cultural and economic facilities in Taiwan, the ministry said. The ministry said that Ousmane will be accompanied by Minister of Foreign Affairs and Cooperation Abdourahman Hama, minister of commerce and transport Abdoulaye Souley and other officials. The ROC and Niger reestablished diplomatic ties in June 1992.
